frameDefinitions: An Agent brings about the end of a Theme's captivity at a Location_of_confinement in contravention of the plans or desires of a captor.
A Captor ends the captivity or inhibition of the motion of a Theme from the Location_of_confinement.
An Agent leaves behind a Theme effectively rendering it no longer within their control or of the normal security as one's property.
A Surrenderer is compelled to transfer a Theme to a Recipient.
In this frame, an Authority allows a Protagonist to know (in some way) that they may or may not engage in an Action.
frameExamples: His accomplice <t>freed</t> him from Sing Sing prison thanks to his disguise.
They <t>released</t> me from prison on New Year's Day.
Carolyn <t>abandoned</t> her car and jumped on a red double decker bus.
Shortly after the boy <t>surrendered</t> the gun, the three remaining warriors made a rush for liberty.
The police officer <t>forbid</t> me from turning around .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual who ends the confinement or captivity of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the person or object in motion released by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The location to which the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion was formerly inhibited.
The <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Agent</fen> release the <fen>Theme</fen> .
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ceases to be confined.
The <fen>Captor</fen> is the individual who ends the confinement or captivity of the <fen>Theme</fen>. The release of the <fen>Theme</fen> is in accord with the plans of the <fen>Captor</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the person or object in motion released by the <fen>Captor</fen>.
The location to which the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion was formerly inhibited.
The <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Captor</fen> release the <fen>Theme</fen> .
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ceases to be confined.
The <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex> is the person who acts to leave behind the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fex name='Theme'>Theme</fex> is the entity that is relinguished to no one from the <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex>'s possession.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The person compelled to transfer the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The object that changes possession.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Surrenderer</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Surrenderer</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Authority</fen> orders the <fen>Protagonist</fen> to not engage in a particular <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> wants to engage in an <fen>Action</fen>, but is ordered not to by the <fen>Authority</fen>.
The <fen>Action</fen> is what the <fen>Protagonist</fen> seeks to do, but is ordered not to.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the denying of permission occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the denial of permission occurs.
listRoleExamples: Rebels set three prisoners free <fex>from holding cells</fex>.
'Aren't you going to free us <fex>here</fex>?' she asked.
She petitioned unsuccessfully for their release <fex>from Chateau D'If</fex>.
'Aren't you going to release us <fex>here</fex>?' she asked.
